				<td colspan="2"><span>I would probably say yes it will remember you since you have only lowered it's hate of you not wiped it's hate list completely, but it's not gonna come after you since you've probably run so far ahead of it that it will just turn away.
<br />

<br />
There is, however, a totally different problem that occurrs in Kunark if you outrun a mob.  The mob has not actually forgotten you, what it does is goes and tells all his friends about you now let's say you outran the mob around the ruins and decide to do some soloing around them later.  Now every mob of that type is going to aggro you and trust me they will come and in numbers.
<br />

<br />
For those that don't believe me I have seen this happen on numerous occasions and can duplicate it easily, how you might ask?
<br />

<br />
1. Run to ridge from FV tunnel, oh make sure you run in aggro range of some spiders and drolvargs.
<br />

<br />
2. Go to R1 and hang out there for about two minutes
<br />

<br />
What you will notice is that spiders and drolvargs will aggro on you from farther away than normal and for no apparent reason.  The really annoying thing here is that zoning doesn't always clear the aggro, however I have been in a few groups where we were loving the extra mobs since we could slice through them like a hot knife through butter.</span></td>
