				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;The really annoying thing here is that zoning doesn't always clear the aggro,&quot;
<br />

<br />
I once thought that zoning ALWAYS clears aggro but, something happened the other day that really freaked me out.
<br />

<br />
I was charmkiting in ME, toilers because I was bored. But I started having too many coming after me instead of my pet (figured out later that you really shouldn't DS your pet...doh!) and I aggroed 2 of those SK/Cleric hooded floaty thingees(Xia Xaui, or something like that) so I decided to hit the afterburners and book to zone. I then zoned back in to see if I can loot some of the half dozen toiler bodies I had scattering the area. I invised and ran in. Halfway to my kiting spot, this toiler from out of nowhere starts making a beeline to me. I was still invised, I wasn't looting anything and toilers do not see invis. So I back out of the way thinking that maybe someone else had aggroed it and just happened to be running my way. Nope. That sucker was coming after me, and I was alone anyways.
<br />

<br />
Something to think about I guess..</span></td>
